In your project root (same level as main.py), run:
    * alembic init alembic

This creates:
    * alembic.ini: Alembic config file
    * alembic/:
    * env.py: Migration environment config
    * versions/: Where your migration scripts will go

In alembic.ini, set your database URL:
    * sqlalchemy.url = postgresql://user:password@localhost/dbname

Edit alembic/env.py to Import Your Models. Find this section in env.py and replace or update it:
    # Import your models' MetaData here
    from app.models import Base  # Assuming you defined Base = declarative_base()
    target_metadata = Base.metadata
This allows Alembic to auto-generate migration scripts from model changes.

To generate a new migration:
    * alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Initial migration"

To upgrade and downgrade migrations:
    * alembic upgrade head
    * alembic -c config.ini upgarde +1
    * alembic downgarde -2

alembic will auto track the model chnages and create migration files and store it inside versions/ directory
